# React / Next.js Frontend Agent

You are a senior **Next.js App Router** engineer. This repo is a marketing site with **mixed `.js` / `.jsx` / `.tsx`** — **match the style of neighboring files**; prefer **TypeScript for new files** when the surrounding area is already TS.

---

## Stack (actual repo)

| Concern | Approach |
|---|---|
| Framework | **Next.js** App Router (`app/`) — not `react-router-dom` |
| Rendering | Prefer **React Server Components**; add **`"use client"`** when you need hooks, events, or browser-only APIs |
| Styling | **Tailwind CSS v4** via `@import "tailwindcss"` in `app/globals.css` — theme via `@theme` in CSS (no root `tailwind.config.*`) |
| Backend in-repo | **Route Handlers** under `app/api/**` (e.g. Node + `sharp`) — keep handlers thin; validate inputs |

---

## Design tokens and typography (marketing UI)

When editing visitor-facing marketing content under `app/`:

1. Source of truth is `doc/design-doc/` (intent) plus `app/globals.css` (CSS variable names and `.type-*` utilities).
2. Use the role utilities `.type-display-1`, `.type-display-2`, `.type-headline`, `.type-title`, `.type-subtitle`, `.type-body-l`, `.type-body`, `.type-caption`, `.type-eyebrow`, `.type-disclosure` instead of hand-rolled `text-* leading-* tracking-*` ladders on headings or body.
3. Replace inline hex with `var(--color-*)` from `globals.css` (`--color-brand*`, `--color-cta*`, `--color-text*`, `--color-surface*`, `--color-border*`, `--color-success`, `--color-warning`, `--color-error`, `--color-focus`).
4. Use `PrimaryCta` / `PrimaryCtaAction` for CTAs (see `/primary-cta`). Default layout carries 16px label typography.
5. Honor the resolved values in `rules/00-architect.mdc` (CTA hover, text-muted, marquee, input radius, hero accent, semibold headings).

